The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Ryerson to scale up output

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, June 1: Tata Ryerson Ltd, the 50:50 joint venture between Tata Steel and US-based Ryerson Tull, plans to double its capacity in the next three years.

 Sandipan Chakravortty, MD of Tata Ryerson (TRL), said the planned expansion of parent Tata Steel and group firm Tata Motors would provide a huge growth opportunity for the company.

 We will more than double the capacity from present 1 million tonne in the next three years as Tata Steel has lined up large projects, he added. 

 Tata Steel accounts for 80 per cent of TRLs business. 

 Tata Motorss high volume projects for its light commercial vehicle, ACE, and the small car will also provide ample scope to grow. TRL will tag along with the firm as its preferred vendor and set up shops in locations where Tata Motors will put up plants like Bengal and Uttranchal. 




